"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Fix: Agent Integration Skill Interface/Naming Drift\n\n## Context\n\nA second-pass audit found 5 issues in the agent integration skill files ‚Äî stale method names, mixed hook/event terminology, ambiguous parameters, missing scope limitation, and a minor reference conflict. These were found after the first audit (7 issues, already fixed). This plan addresses the verified findings.\n\n## Verification of Findings\n\n### Finding 1: CONFIRMED HIGH ‚Äî Stale method names in implementer.md\n\n**Step 3 (line 38)** lists 11 `Agent` interface methods but the actual interface has 15. Missing:\n- `GetSessionID(input *HookInput) string`\n- `ReadSession(input *HookInput) (*AgentSession, error)`\n- `WriteSession(ctx context.Context, session *AgentSession) error`\n- `FormatResumeCommand(sessionID string) string`\n\n**Step 5 (line 91) and line 105** use wrong `TranscriptAnalyzer` method names:\n| implementer.md says | Actual method in agent.go |\n|---|---|\n| `ExtractFilesTouched` | `ExtractModifiedFilesFromOffset` |\n| `ExtractUserPrompts` | `ExtractPrompts` |\n| `GenerateContext` | `ExtractSummary` |\n| *(missing)* | `GetTranscriptPosition` |\n\n### Finding 2: CONFIRMED HIGH ‚Äî Mixed hook/event names in implementer.md\n\nLines 65, 79, 88 use Claude Code-specific native hook names where EventType names should be used:\n| implementer.md says | Should say (EventType) |\n|---|---|\n| `Stop` (lines 65, 79, 88) | `TurnEnd` (or `SessionEnd`) |\n| `UserPromptSubmit` (line 88) | `TurnStart` |\n| `SubagentTaskStart`/`SubagentTaskEnd` (line 88) | `SubagentStart`/`SubagentEnd` |\n\nThese are agent-specific hook verbs, not normalized EventType values. An implementer following these literally for a non-Claude agent would assert on wrong types.\n\n### Finding 3: CONFIRMED MEDIUM ‚Äî AGENT_SLUG ambiguity\n\nReal-world evidence from Gemini:\n- Go package dir: `geminicli/` (no hyphen ‚Äî Go requires this)\n- Agent registry key (AgentName): `\"gemini\"`\n- E2E Name(): `\"gemini-cli\"`\n- E2E_AGENT filter: `\"gemini-cli\"`\n\nA single `AGENT_SLUG` can't serve all four roles. If set to `\"gemini\"`, the E2E filter is wrong. If set to `\"gemini-cli\"`, it's an invalid Go package name.\n\n### Finding 4: CONFIRMED MEDIUM ‚Äî Hook-only scope not declared\n\nimplementer.md Step 3 (line 41) mandates `hooks.go` with `InstallHooks`/`UninstallHooks`/`AreHooksInstalled`. Step 4 starts with hook-exercising tests. But `agent.go:111` defines `FileWatcher` as an alternative integration path. The skill doesn't mention FileWatcher or scope itself to hook-capable agents.\n\n### Finding 5: CONFIRMED LOW ‚Äî Checklist reference conflict\n\nSKILL.md:31 lists `agent-integration-checklist.md` in Architecture References. researcher.md:11 says \"Do NOT read ... checklist.\" Mild confusion for the researcher phase.\n\n---\n\n## Design Principle: Reference Source, Don't Hardcode\n\nThe root cause of findings 1-3 is hardcoded names that drift from the source code. The fix pattern is:\n- **Never list method names** ‚Äî say \"all methods from the `Agent` interface in `agent.go`\"\n- **Never list EventType values** ‚Äî say \"use `EventType` constants from `event.go`\"\n- **Point to existing agents** as examples of naming patterns rather than encoding naming rules\n\nThis means the skill files age gracefully ‚Äî when interfaces change, the implementer reads the current source.\n\n---\n\n## Fixes\n\n### Fix 1: Remove hardcoded method lists from implementer.md (Findings 1 & 2)\n\n**File:** `.claude/skills/agent-integration/implementer.md`\n\n**Step 3 (line 38)** ‚Äî Replace the parenthetical method list with a source reference:\n\n```\n- (Name, Type, Description, IsPreview, DetectPresence, ProtectedDirs, GetSessionDir, ResolveSessionFile, ReadTranscript, ChunkTranscript, ReassembleTranscript).\n+ (every method in the `Agent` interface ‚Äî refer to `agent.go` from Step 1). Include `HookSupport` methods in `lifecycle.go` and `hooks.go`.\n```\n\n**Step 5 line 